    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. Test conditions factor (Gradation 2 achieved vs. Gradation 3 required) is a known gap; risk accepted given full ASTM F1717 compliance, regulatory precedent for single-condition testing, and corroborating inter-laboratory reproducibility. E/uval metrics for all three primary QoIs are within the pre-specified acceptance bound of 1.96. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
